cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB

This paper deals with the tradeoff between privacy and utility in differential privacy, which is a topic closely related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of linear programming and optimization techniques (cs.IT), as well as machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The study of differential privacy also has connections to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
